Escherichia coli 16S Ribosomal RNA

The 16S rRNA gene is a highly conserved bacterial marker used for bacterial identification and phylogenetic analysis. It contains conserved and hypervariable regions important for taxonomy.

This sequence is ideal for multiple sequence alignment, phylogenetic tree construction, BLAST analysis, and microbiome-related projects. It is one of the most commonly studied nucleotide sequences in bioinformatics.
